    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "deviceClass": "Class II"
  },
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/fea-construct-performance-claim-001",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "FEA accurately predicts compression-bending performance of non-cannulated pedicle screw construct",
      "description": "The FEA modeling framework, implemented independently by three organizations (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes), accurately predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending loading conditions. Predictions fall within 10% of experimental mean values across all three quantities of interest, and the normalized validation metric E/uval remains below 1.96 for each QoI. This claim is grounded in a comprehensive body of work encompassing mesh convergence studies, material property characterization from coupon testing, contact algorithm verification, and direct comparison against N=11 physical constructs tested at two independent laboratories. The multi-lab experimental program and the three-organization modeling exercise together provide strong corroborating evidence that the model is fit for its intended purpose at Medium credibility level.",
      "purpose": "Support regulatory submission demonstrating FEA model credibility for predicting non-cannulated pedicle screw construct mechanical performance under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending.",
      "scope": "Non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct; ASTM F1717 static compression-bending; construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement; Medium model risk level."
    }
  ],
