  "signature": "ed25519:b7e3a1f9c2d4b6e8a0c5f3d1b9e7a4c2f0d8b6e4a2c0f8d6b4e2a0c8f6d4b2e0",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA software used in this analysis must be validated per vendor QMS and have documented version control, regression testing, and audit trail. Required Gradation 2 (documented QMS with periodic audits).",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022R2 and Abaqus 2021 both carry ISO 9001-certified QMS documentation, automated regression test suites covering structural analysis modules, and traceable version control. FDA in-house code additionally subject to CDRH software validation SOP. Achieved Gradation 3 (independent verification of test suite completeness)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA code must reproduce analytical benchmark solutions for beam bending and contact problems to within 1% relative error. Required Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "All three FEA implementations verified against Timoshenko beam bending analytical solution and Hertzian contact benchmark. Maximum relative error 0.7%. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate QoI change less than 2% between successive mesh refinements. GCI must be reported. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study performed across four mesh densities (coarse to fine: 0.8 mm, 0.5 mm, 0.3 mm, 0.2 mm element size at screw-rod interface). Richardson extrapolation applied; GCI < 0.8% for all three QoIs. Asymptotic convergence confirmed. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals must fall below 1e-6 for force and displacement norms. Time-step sensitivity study required for quasi-static ramp. Required Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear quasi-static analyses converged with force residual norm below 1e-7 and displacement norm below 1e-8 in all load steps. Load-step sensitivity study confirmed less than 0.3% QoI variation between 100 and 500 load increments. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model setup must be independently reviewed by a second analyst; boundary condition application and material assignment must be documented in a traceable model specification document. Required Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Each of the three modeling teams performed internal peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments against a shared model specification document. Discrepancies identified during cross-organization comparison were resolved and documented. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The governing equations, constitutive models, and contact formulations must be appropriate for the physical phenomena of interest (large-displacement elastoplastic bending with frictional contact). Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Large-displacement nonlinear analysis with elastoplastic Ti-6Al-4V material model (bilinear isotropic hardening, yield stress 880 MPa, tangent modulus 1.2 GPa) and frictional contact (Coulomb, mu=0.2) at screw-rod and rod-UHMWPE block interfaces. Model form selection justified by comparison to published literature on pedicle screw construct mechanics. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties must be derived from coupon testing of the same material lot used in construct testing. Geometric dimensions must be measured from actual test articles. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material properties (E=114 GPa, yield 880 MPa, UTS 950 MPa) measured from dog-bone coupons machined from the same bar stock as the test constructs. UHMWPE block properties from literature (E=0.8 GPa). Screw and rod geometry from CMM measurements of five test articles (mean ± SD reported). Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental sample size must be sufficient to characterize population variability; samples must be from production lots representative of the intended device. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-representative non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screws and 5.5 mm Ti rods. Constructs distributed across two independent laboratories (Lab 1: n=6; Lab 2: n=5). Coefficient of variation for stiffness 4.4%, yield force 3.9%, force at 40 mm 4.5% — consistent with published variability for this construct type. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing must cover the range of loading conditions representative of the COU, including at least two load levels or configurations. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 static compression-bending configuration only. Dynamic and fatigue conditions not included in this validation activity. This factor is below the required level; the shortfall is acknowledged and accepted given that the COU is limited to static compression-bending prediction. Gradation 2 achieved against required Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters must be demonstrably equivalent to experimental conditions; any deviations must be quantified and shown to have negligible effect on QoIs. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Torque applied to set screws during construct assembly measured and replicated in FEA as prescribed preload (8 Nm). Crosshead displacement rate (25 mm/min) reproduced as quasi-static ramp. UHMWPE block geometry measured and matched in FEA. Sensitivity analysis confirmed that ±10% variation in set-screw preload produces less than 1.5% change in any QoI. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric must account for both model prediction error and experimental uncertainty; E/uval < 1.96 required for each QoI. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Normalized validation metric E/uval computed for each QoI incorporating experimental standard uncertainty (measurement system uncertainty + sample variability) and model numerical uncertainty (GCI). Results: stiffness E/uval=0.41, yield force E/uval=0.63, force at 40 mm E/uval=0.28. All below 1.96 threshold. Percent differences all below 10%. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
