      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs evaluated in validation must be directly relevant to the clinical and regulatory decision being supported. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three primary QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly relevant to the regulatory submission for the non-cannulated pedicle screw. These QoIs are used by FDA reviewers to assess construct mechanical performance. Gradation 3 achieved."
